Product Comparison

This project aims to compare the prices of a product on two different e-commerce websites, Amazon and Flipkart, based on the product name. The data sets used for training and testing the model are amz_com-ecommerce_sample.csv and flipkart_com-ecommerce_sample.csv.

Getting Started
These instructions will get you a copy of the project up and running on your local machine for development and testing purposes.

Prerequisites
You need to have Python 3.x and the following libraries installed on your system:

spacy
scipy
pandas
You can install these libraries using pip:


pip install spacy scipy pandas
You also need to download the en_core_web_lg model for spaCy:


python -m spacy download en_core_web_lg
Installing
Clone the repository and navigate to the project directory:


git clone https://github.com/your-username/Product-Comparison.git
cd Product-Comparison
Usage
To run the project, execute the following command in the project directory:


python product_comparison.py
When prompted, enter the product name that you want to compare the prices of on the two websites.

